The paper deals with the design of error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of spatially-coupled codes is a common technique in coding theory, which falls under the category of coding and information theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the girth properties of the codes, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.DS). The potential applications of the codes in data storage systems suggest that the paper may also fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.SI).
